About the Dietary Strategy

This dietary plan has been created based on the food history assessment, the energy requirements associated with all of your activities, including physical exercise, and your food preferences.

Initially, I recommend weighing all foods raw and without waste. Over time, you will learn to estimate portion sizes without needing a scale. I have created a dietary plan that allows you to freely choose from the proposed meals every day, based on your tastes, time available, and food availability.

In this regard, by respecting the suggested quantities, you can consume the same percentage of calories by combining different foods from day to day. Remember to alternate snacks, main dishes, and side dishes between lunch and dinner, and from one day to the next. This will not only prevent the daily repetition of foods but also avoid the accumulation of substances in the intestines, which over time could lead to the development of adverse reactions to foods consumed too frequently.

It is crucial to consider each food as medicine, necessary for your body in the recommended doses and timing.

Remember, it is essential to have breakfast within an hour of waking up, and to wait no more than 3-4 hours between meals and snacks, as well as between one snack and the next meal. It is important to always consume your snacks and never skip from one meal to another with a 6-7 hour fast! This will help maintain a stable blood sugar concentration, preventing blood sugar spikes and the subsequent rise in insulin hormone levels, which are responsible for the development of diet-related diabetes. Furthermore, this will prevent uncontrolled hunger and allow you to reach mealtimes calmly.

Start to see your diet as a means to not only reach your ideal weight but, more importantly, to achieve a psychological and physical well-being that can be integrated into every moment of your day thanks to the daily changes that the new eating style will bring to your body and mind.<|user|>